			<div class="blog-faq"><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What is the main difference between a lip lift and lip fillers?</h3>
					<p>A lip lift is a surgical procedure that permanently elevates the upper lip by removing excess skin beneath the nose, while lip fillers are non-surgical injections that temporarily add volume to the lips. The lip lift addresses structural aging, while fillers add volume without changing lip position.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long do lip fillers last?</h3>
					<p>Hyaluronic acid lip fillers typically last six to twelve months, depending on the product used, the treatment area, and individual factors such as metabolism. Some patients may experience longer or shorter duration based on their lifestyle and the amount of filler used.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Is a lip lift permanent?</h3>
					<p>Yes, a lip lift provides permanent results. Once the excess skin is removed and the lip is elevated, the improvement in lip position and visible pink lip area is long-lasting. However, the natural aging process continues, and some patients may eventually desire additional procedures.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long is recovery from a lip lift?</h3>
					<p>Most patients experience swelling and bruising for seven to ten days after a lip lift. You can typically return to normal activities after one to two weeks. The scar takes several months to fully mature and fade, but it is well-concealed beneath the nose.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Can I get a lip lift and fillers together?</h3>
					<p>Yes, many patients combine a lip lift with fillers to achieve comprehensive lip enhancement. The lip lift addresses the structural position of the lip, while fillers can add volume and definition. Dr. Johar can create a customized treatment plan that addresses all your concerns.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Which procedure is more cost-effective?</h3>
					<p>While lip fillers have a lower upfront cost, the need for regular maintenance sessions can make them more expensive over time. A lip lift, though more expensive initially, provides permanent results that may be more cost-effective in the long run. Dr. Johar discusses pricing during your consultation to help you make an informed decision.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Are lip fillers safe?</h3>
					<p>When performed by an experienced, board-certified plastic surgeon like Dr. Johar, lip fillers are generally safe. Hyaluronic acid fillers are reversible, providing an additional safety measure. Risks include bruising, swelling, and rare complications such as vascular occlusion, which Dr. Johar takes every precaution to prevent.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
